    <section id="philosophy" class="py-14 border-b border-border scroll-mt-16 print:hidden" aria-labelledby="philosophy-heading">
      <h2 id="philosophy-heading" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-3 reveal">
        <!-- lightbulb icon -->
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 21h6m-6-4h6M12 3a6 6 0 0 1 4.472 10.074A3 3 0 0 0 15 16H9a3 3 0 0 0-1.472-2.926A6 6 0 0 1 12 3Z"/></svg>
        How I Approach Engineering
      </h2>
      <p class="max-w-2xl text-text-secondary mb-8 reveal">A few things that shape how I design and build systems — all visible in the projects above.</p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-7 reveal-stagger">
        <div class="bg-bg-elevated border border-border rounded-xl p-5">
          <!-- minimize / simplicity icon -->
          <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 border border-accent/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <svg class="w-4.5 h-4.5 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 12h14"/></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold mb-1.5">Simplicity over cleverness</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">I default to the boring, well-understood solution and only reach for complexity when the problem actually demands it. Code that's easy to delete is easier to maintain than code that's clever.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-bg-elevated border border-border rounded-xl p-5">
          <!-- shield / resilience icon -->
          <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 border border-accent/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <svg class="w-4.5 h-4.5 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10Z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold mb-1.5">Design for failure, not just the happy path</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Dropped connections and stale state aren't edge cases — they're normal operating conditions for real users, which is why I build offline-first and let systems degrade gracefully by default.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-bg-elevated border border-border rounded-xl p-5">
          <!-- cog / automation icon -->
          <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 border border-accent/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <svg class="w-4.5 h-4.5 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.325 4.317c.426-1.756 2.924-1.756 3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 0 0 2.573 1.066c1.543-.94 3.31.826 2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 0 0 1.065 2.572c1.756.426 1.756 2.924 0 3.35a1.724 1.724 0 0 0-1.066 2.573c.94 1.543-.826 3.31-2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 0 0-2.572 1.065c-.426 1.756-2.924 1.756-3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 0 0-2.573-1.066c-1.543.94-3.31-.826-2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 0 0-1.065-2.572c-1.756-.426-1.756-2.924 0-3.35a1.724 1.724 0 0 0 1.066-2.573c-.94-1.543.826-3.31 2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 0 0 2.572-1.065Z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold mb-1.5">Automate the repeatable</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Linting, formatting, compliance reports, pre-commit gates — anything a human shouldn't have to remember by hand gets automated, so review time goes to logic instead of style.</p>
        </div>
